      "message": "[Critical] Line 34: This uses `originalPriority` to decide whether the app should perform full wake-up processing, but FCM can downgrade high-priority messages; `originalPriority` still reports the sender\u0027s requested priority, while `priority` reflects the delivered priority. A downgraded message would still acquire the WakeLock/start daemon work, defeating the purpose of skipping normal-priority deliveries. Use the effective priority instead.\n```suggestion\n        val isHigh \u003d remoteMessage.priority \u003d\u003d RemoteMessage.PRIORITY_HIGH\n```",
